description: As the name itself suggests, Clustering algorithms group a set of data points into subsets or clusters. The algorithms' goal is to create clusters that are coherent internally, but clearly different from each other externally. In other words, entities within a cluster should be as similar as possible and entities in one cluster should be as dissimilar as possible from entities in another.
